{"text": "The name aldol is derived from the names of the two functional groups, aldehyde and alcohol, present in the products.", "fibs": ["name"]}
{"text": "The aldol and ketol readily lose water to give α,β-unsaturated carbonyl compounds which are aldol condensation products and the reaction is called Aldol condensation.", "fibs": ["aldol"]}
{"text": "Though ketones give ketols (compounds containing a keto and alcohol groups), the general name aldol condensation still applies to the reactions of ketones due to their similarity with aldehydes.", "fibs": ["keto"]}
{"text": "(ii) Cross aldol condensation: When aldol condensation is carried out between two different aldehydes and / or ketones, it is called cross aldol condensation.", "fibs": ["ii"]}
{"text": "If both of them contain α-hydrogen atoms, it gives a mixture of four products.", "fibs": ["mixture"]}
{"text": "This is illustrated below by aldol reaction of a mixture of ethanal and propanal.", "fibs": ["aldol"]}
